{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016DBRdKZdydiSf2niGRBki5","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Role\n2\t\n3\tYou are executing one step of a multi-PRD repo extraction. The PRD you\n4\tare implementing operates on a **separate target repository** on disk\n5\t(e.g. `~/Developer/darkfactory`), not on the pumice repo where you are\n6\tcurrently checked out.\n7\t\n8\tThe harness has created a pumice-side worktree for status tracking and\n9\tcommit accounting, but the actual file changes happen in the target\n10\trepo. You may `cd` into the target repo, run shell commands there, and\n11\tedit files there freely.\n12\t\n13\t## Your responsibilities\n14\t\n15\t1. Read the target PRD carefully — Requirements, Technical Approach,\n16\t   Acceptance Criteria.\n17\t2. Carry out the steps in the target repository the PRD names. This may\n18\t   include cloning, running `git filter-repo`, scaffolding files,\n19\t   pushing branches, etc.\n20\t3. Verify against the PRD's Acceptance Criteria. Use whatever tools the\n21\t   target repo provides (`pytest`, `mypy`, `git log`, etc.) — there is\n22\t   no pumice-side `just test` for this work.\n23\t4. Stage and commit any pumice-side changes (typically just the PRD\n24\t   status update) with a conventional-commits message.\n25\t\n26\t## You MUST NOT\n27\t\n28\t- Modify pumice source code unless the PRD explicitly requires it.\n29\t- Push or open PRs in the target repo unless the PRD says so — the\n30\t  harness handles the pumice-side push/PR.\n31\t- Run destructive commands outside the scope of the PRD.\n32\t- Bypass commit hooks with `--no-verify`.\n33\t\n34\t## Sentinel contract\n35\t\n36\tYour **final line** must be exactly one of:\n37\t\n38\t- `PRD_EXECUTE_OK: {{PRD_ID}}` — work complete, ACs verified.\n39\t- `PRD_EXECUTE_FAILED: <reason>` — blocker; describe in one line.\n40\t\n[result-id: r19]"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017x74usEsvHbE9fPYD9WHc8","session_id":"139194c3-2b15-46fb-ae47-01a4e87ddf0a","uuid":"bbd35253-4850-4206-9cb0-6d0474626cfa","timestamp":"2026-04-08T14:41:44.519Z"}
