{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GGxZaQBUPc4yUSoXZkLbis","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Workflow assignment logic.\n2\t\n3\tGiven a PRD and a set of loaded workflows, decide which workflow should\n4\trun for it. The resolution priority is:\n5\t\n6\t1. **Explicit frontmatter field**: if ``prd.workflow`` is set and names\n7\t   a loaded workflow, return it unconditionally. This lets authors\n8\t   pin a specific workflow to a specific PRD, overriding any predicate\n9\t   matching.\n10\t2. **applies_to predicates**: otherwise, evaluate every workflow's\n11\t   :attr:`~darkfactory.workflow.Workflow.applies_to` predicate and pick\n12\t   the highest-priority workflow that returns truthy. Ties are broken\n13\t   alphabetically by workflow name for determinism.\n14\t3. **Default fallback**: if no predicate matches, return the\n15\t   ``default`` workflow. If there's no default either, raise\n16\t   ``KeyError``.\n17\t\n18\tThe two-argument ``applies_to(prd, prds)`` signature is preferred, but\n19\tsingle-arg legacy lambdas (``lambda prd: ...``) are tolerated via a\n20\t``TypeError`` fallback — workflows authored before the signature\n21\texpansion keep working.\n22\t\n23\t``assign_all`` is a convenience for bulk resolution across a whole PRD\n24\tset, used by the ``prd assign`` CLI subcommand.\n25\t\"\"\"\n26\t\n27\tfrom __future__ import annotations\n28\t\n29\tfrom typing import Any\n30\t\n31\tfrom .prd import PRD\n32\tfrom .workflow import Workflow\n33\t\n34\t\n35\tdef assign_workflow(\n36\t    prd: PRD,\n37\t    prds: dict[str, PRD],\n38\t    workflows: dict[str, Workflow],\n39\t) -> Workflow:\n40\t    \"\"\"Resolve the workflow for a single PRD.\n41\t\n42\t    See the module docstring for resolution priority. Raises ``KeyError``\n43\t    only if no workflow matches *and* there's no ``default`` workflow in\n44\t    the set — which is a misconfiguration the caller should catch and\n45\t    surface (missing default workflow is a deployment problem, not a\n46\t    per-PRD problem).\n47\t    \"\"\"\n48\t    # 1. Explicit frontmatter field wins.\n49\t    if prd.workflow and prd.workflow in workflows:\n50\t        return workflows[prd.workflow]\n51\t\n52\t    # 2. Predicate match by priority, alphabetical tie-break for determinism.\n53\t    matches = [w for w in workflows.values() if _matches(w, prd, prds)]\n54\t    if matches:\n55\t        matches.sort(key=lambda w: (-w.priority, w.name))\n56\t        return matches[0]\n57\t\n58\t    # 3. Fall back to default.\n59\t    if \"default\" in workflows:\n60\t        return workflows[\"default\"]\n61\t\n62\t    raise KeyError(\n63\t        f\"no workflow matches {prd.id!r} and no 'default' workflow is registered\"\n64\t    )\n65\t\n66\t\n67\tdef assign_all(\n68\t    prds: dict[str, PRD],\n69\t    workflows: dict[str, Workflow],\n70\t) -> dict[str, Workflow]:\n71\t    \"\"\"Resolve workflow assignments for every PRD in ``prds``.\n72\t\n73\t    Returns a dict keyed by PRD id. Used by ``prd assign`` to dump the\n74\t    full assignment table and optionally persist it to frontmatter via\n75\t    ``--write``. Propagates ``KeyError`` from :func:`assign_workflow` if\n76\t    any single PRD has no match and there's no default.\n77\t    \"\"\"\n78\t    return {\n79\t        prd_id: assign_workflow(prd, prds, workflows) for prd_id, prd in prds.items()\n80\t    }\n[result-id: r22]"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017x74usEsvHbE9fPYD9WHc8","session_id":"139194c3-2b15-46fb-ae47-01a4e87ddf0a","uuid":"d6690a59-d03a-42fb-b21b-fd2a59530574","timestamp":"2026-04-08T14:41:49.582Z"}
