{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017x74usEsvHbE9fPYD9WHc8","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me compile my final report.\n\n## Comprehensive DarkFactory Codebase Exploration Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the DarkFactory codebase to understand the planning workflow implementation requirements. Here's the complete analysis:\n\n### 1. DIRECTORY STRUCTURE\n\n**Workflows Location:** `/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-228-planning-workflow-initial/workflows/`\n\nExisting workflows:\n- `workflows/default/` - General-purpose catchall workflow\n  - `workflow.py` - Task list with implementation pattern\n  - `prompts/role.md` - Role definition for agents\n  - `prompts/task.md` - Task instructions\n  - `prompts/verify.md` - Retry instructions after shell failures\n- `workflows/extraction/` - Special workflow for separate target repos\n  - `workflow.py` - Similar structure but no test/lint phase\n  - `prompts/role.md`, `task.md`, `verify.md`\n\n**Core Source:** `/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-228-planning-workflow-initial/src/darkfactory/`\n\n### 2. CORE CLASSES AND FUNCTION SIGNATURES\n\n#### `workflow.py` - Task Types and Workflow Definition\n\n**`BuiltIn` (dataclass):**\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass BuiltIn(Task):\n    name: str\n    kwargs: dict[str, Any] = field(default_factory=dict)\n```\n- References deterministic SDLC primitives by name\n- Example: `BuiltIn(\"commit\", kwargs={\"message\": \"chore(prd): {prd_id} start work\"})`\n\n**`AgentTask` (dataclass):**\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass AgentTask(Task):\n    name: str = \"implement\"\n    prompts: list[str] = field(default_factory=list)\n    tools: list[str] = field(default_factory=list)\n    model: str | None = None\n    model_from_capability: bool = True\n    retries: int = 1\n    verify_prompts: list[str] = field(default_factory=list)\n    sentinel_success: str = \"PRD_EXECUTE_OK\"\n    sentinel_failure: str = \"PRD_EXECUTE_FAILED\"\n```\n- Invokes Claude Code with prompts and tool allowlist\n- Model selection: explicit via `model` or mapped from `capability` if `model_from_capability=True`\n- Sentinel line parsing determines success/failure\n\n**`ShellTask` (dataclass):**\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass ShellTask(Task):\n    name: str\n    cmd: str\n    on_failure: OnFailure = \"fail\"  # \"fail\" | \"retry_agent\" | \"ignore\"\n    env: dict[str, str] = field(default_factory=dict)\n```\n- Runs deterministic shell commands in the worktree\n- `on_failure=\"retry_agent\"` triggers re-invocation of preceding AgentTask with verify prompts\n\n**`Workflow` (dataclass):**\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass Workflow:\n    name: str\n    description: str = \"\"\n    applies_to: AppliesToPredicate = field(default=_default_applies_to)\n    priority: int = 0\n    tasks: list[Task] = field(default_factory=list)\n    workflow_dir: Path | None = None\n```\n- `applies_to` signature: `Callable[[PRD, dict[str, PRD]], bool]` - two arguments (PRD + full PRD set)\n- Priority ordering: higher numbers win; same priority → alphabetical by name\n- `workflow_dir` is set by the loader to resolve prompt paths\n\n**`ExecutionContext` (dataclass):**\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass ExecutionContext:\n    prd: \"PRD\"\n    repo_root: Path\n    workflow: Workflow\n    base_ref: str\n    branch_name: str\n    worktree_path: Path | None = None\n    cwd: Path = field(default_factory=Path.cwd)\n    agent_output: str | None = None\n    agent_success: bool = False\n    pr_url: str | None = None\n    dry_run: bool = True\n    logger: logging.Logger = field(default_factory=...)\n    _worktree_lock: \"FileLock | None\" = field(default=None, repr=False)\n\ndef format_string(self, template: str) -> str:\n    # Supports: {prd_id}, {prd_title}, {prd_slug}, {branch}, {base_ref}, {worktree}\n```\n\n#### `containment.py` - Tree Navigation Functions\n\n```python\ndef children(prd_id: str, prds: dict[str, PRD]) -> list[PRD]:\n    \"\"\"Direct children of prd_id, naturally sorted.\"\"\"\n\ndef descendants(prd_id: str, prds: dict[str, PRD]) -> list[PRD]:\n    \"\"\"All transitive children, BFS order.\"\"\"\n\ndef ancestors(prd_id: str, prds: dict[str, PRD]) -> list[PRD]:\n    \"\"\"Walk up parent chain from immediate to root.\"\"\"\n\ndef roots(prds: dict[str, PRD]) -> list[PRD]:\n    \"\"\"Top-level PRDs with no parent, naturally sorted.\"\"\"\n\ndef is_leaf(prd: PRD, prds: dict[str, PRD]) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"True if prd has no children.\"\"\"\n\ndef is_fully_decomposed(prd: PRD, prds: dict[str, PRD]) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"True if prd has at least one task-kind descendant.\n    \n    Returns: any(d.kind == \"task\" for d in descendants(prd.id, prds))\n    \"\"\"\n\ndef is_runnable(prd: PRD, prds: dict[str, PRD]) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"True if prd can be executed by an implementation workflow.\n    \n    A PRD is runnable when: (prd.kind == \"task\") OR is_leaf(prd, prds)\n    Containers with children are NOT runnable; they use planning workflow instead.\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n### 3. CLI STRUCTURE\n\n**Key Commands in `cli.py`:**\n\n- `cmd_list_workflows(args)` - Line 572\n  - Lists all loaded workflows sorted by descending priority, then alphabetically\n  - Supports `--json` output\n  - Returns dict with: `name`, `priority`, `description`, `task_count`, `workflow_dir`\n\n- `cmd_assign(args)` - Line 610\n  - Computes workflow assignment for every PRD\n  - Uses `assign.assign_workflow(prd, prds, workflows)` for resolution\n  - With `--write` flag, persists assignment to frontmatter (only for PRDs without explicit workflow field)\n\n- `cmd_plan(args)` - Line 798\n  - Shows execution plan without touching anything\n  - Resolves workflow, computes branch name + base ref + model\n  - Prints ordered task list with descriptions\n  - `--workflow` override, `--base` ref override, `--model` override available\n  - Supports `--json` output\n\n- `cmd_run(args)` - Line 880\n  - Defaults to dry-run; `--execute` flag for live mode\n  - Calls `run_workflow()` from `runner.py`\n  - Runnability check only applies in `--execute` mode (dry-run allowed for discovery)\n\n**Assignment Logic in `assign.py`:**\n\n```python\ndef assign_workflow(prd: PRD, prds: dict[str, PRD], workflows: dict[str, Workflow]) -> Workflow:\n    \"\"\"Priority order:\n    1. Explicit prd.workflow field (if set and loaded)\n    2. applies_to predicates (highest priority wins; ties break alphabetically)\n    3. Default workflow fallback\n    Raises KeyError if no match and no default.\n    \"\"\"\n\ndef assign_all(prds: dict[str, PRD], workflows: dict[str, Workflow]) -> dict[str, Workflow]:\n    \"\"\"Bulk assignment for every PRD.\"\"\"\n```\n\n### 4. LOADER PATTERN\n\n**`loader.py` - Dynamic Workflow Discovery:**\n\n```python\ndef load_workflows(workflows_dir: Path) -> dict[str, Workflow]:\n    \"\"\"Scan workflows_dir for subdirectories containing workflow.py.\n    \n    - Each subdir is a potential workflow\n    - Skips dirs starting with _ or .\n    - Imports workflow.py with synthetic module name\n    - Expects top-level 'workflow' attribute of type Workflow\n    - Sets workflow.workflow_dir to subdirectory path\n    - Returns dict keyed by workflow.name\n    - Raises ValueError on duplicate names\n    - Logs warnings for import errors (doesn't fail)\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n### 5. PRD DATACLASS AND PARSING\n\n**`prd.py` - PRD Structure:**\n\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass PRD:\n    id: str\n    path: Path\n    slug: str\n    title: str\n    kind: str  # \"epic\", \"feature\", \"task\"\n    status: str  # \"draft\", \"ready\", \"in-progress\", \"review\", \"done\", \"blocked\", \"cancelled\"\n    priority: str\n    effort: str\n    capability: str  # \"trivial\", \"simple\", \"moderate\", \"complex\"\n    parent: str | None  # PRD id of parent (containment, not dependency)\n    depends_on: list[str]  # PRD ids (dependency DAG)\n    blocks: list[str]  # PRD ids that this blocks\n    impacts: list[str]  # File patterns affected\n    workflow: str | None  # Explicit workflow assignment\n    assignee: str | None\n    reviewers: list[str]\n    target_version: str | None\n    created: date | str\n    updated: date | str\n    tags: list[str]\n    raw_frontmatter: dict[str, Any]  # Original YAML dict\n    body: str  # Body content (preserved byte-for-byte)\n\n# Helper functions:\ndef parse_wikilink(value: str | None) -> str | None:\n    \"\"\"Extract bare PRD id from [[PRD-NNN-slug]] format.\"\"\"\n\ndef parse_wikilinks(values: list[str] | None) -> list[str]:\n    \"\"\"Extract multiple PRD ids from wikilink list.\"\"\"\n\ndef parse_prd(path: Path) -> PRD:\n    \"\"\"Parse single PRD file from disk.\"\"\"\n\ndef load_all(prd_dir: Path) -> dict[str, PRD]:\n    \"\"\"Load all PRD-*.md files (skips _template.md), keyed by id.\"\"\"\n\ndef dump_frontmatter(fm: dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Serialize frontmatter dict back to YAML preserving key order.\"\"\"\n```\n\n### 6. EXISTING TEST PATTERNS\n\n**`test_containment.py`:**\n- Tests all containment functions: `children`, `descendants`, `ancestors`, `roots`, `is_leaf`, `is_fully_decomposed`, `is_runnable`\n- Uses `write_prd()` fixture helper to create test PRDs\n- Demonstrates nested epic→feature→task hierarchies\n\n**`test_workflow.py`:**\n- Tests `BuiltIn`, `AgentTask`, `ShellTask` construction\n- Tests `Workflow` construction with custom `applies_to` predicates\n- Tests `ExecutionContext.format_string()` placeholder expansion\n\n**`test_cli_workflows.py`:**\n- Tests `list-workflows` and `assign` subcommands\n- Shows fixture workflow creation pattern\n- Tests JSON output modes\n\n### 7. WORKFLOW EXAMPLES\n\n**Default Workflow (7 tasks):**\n1. `BuiltIn(\"ensure_worktree\")`\n2. `BuiltIn(\"set_status\", kwargs={\"to\": \"in-progress\"})`\n3. `BuiltIn(\"commit\", kwargs={\"message\": \"chore(prd): {prd_id} start work\"})`\n4. `AgentTask(name=\"implement\", prompts=[...], tools=[...], model_from_capability=True, retries=1, verify_prompts=[...])`\n5. `ShellTask(\"test\", cmd=\"just test\", on_failure=\"retry_agent\")`\n6. `ShellTask(\"format\", cmd=\"just format\", on_failure=\"fail\")`\n7. `ShellTask(\"lint\", cmd=\"just lint format-check\", on_failure=\"retry_agent\")`\n8. `ShellTask(\"typecheck\", cmd=\"just typecheck\", on_failure=\"retry_agent\")`\n9. `BuiltIn(\"set_status\", kwargs={\"to\": \"review\"})`\n10. `BuiltIn(\"commit\", kwargs={\"message\": \"chore(prd): {prd_id} ready for review\"})`\n11. `BuiltIn(\"push_branch\")`\n12. `BuiltIn(\"create_pr\")`\n\n**Extraction Workflow (6 tasks):**\n- Same structure but: no test/lint/format/typecheck shells, uses broad `Bash` tool, works on separate target repo\n\n### 8. PROMPT FILE PATTERNS\n\n**Standard Three-File Pattern:**\n- `prompts/role.md` - Short role definition, responsibilities, constraints (don't-do list), sentinel contract\n- `prompts/task.md` - Step-by-step instructions with placeholders like `{{PRD_ID}}`, `{{PRD_PATH}}`, `{{WORKTREE_PATH}}`, `{{BRANCH_NAME}}`, `{{BASE_REF}}`\n- `prompts/verify.md` - Retry instructions used when `on_failure=\"retry_agent\"`, receives `{{CHECK_OUTPUT}}` binding\n\n**Template Placeholders (in prompts):**\n- `{{PRD_ID}}` - e.g. \"PRD-228\"\n- `{{PRD_TITLE}}` - e.g. \"Initial planning workflow\"\n- `{{PRD_PATH}}` - Absolute path to PRD markdown file\n- `{{WORKTREE_PATH}}` - Worktree root directory\n- `{{BRANCH_NAME}}` - Feature branch name\n- `{{BASE_REF}}` - Base reference branch\n- `{{CHECK_OUTPUT}}` - Failed shell output (only in verify prompts)\n\n### 9. PRD-228 REQUIREMENTS SUMMARY\n\nFor the planning workflow implementation, PRD-228 specifies:\n\n**Predicate Matching:**\n- `prd.kind in (\"epic\", \"feature\")`\n- `prd.status == \"ready\"`\n- `not is_fully_decomposed(prd, prds)` (no task descendants)\n\n**Priority:** 5 (above default 0, below ui-component 10)\n\n**Model:** Pinned to `opus` with `model_from_capability=False`\n\n**Tool Allowlist:**\n- Read, Glob, Grep - read existing PRDs\n- Write - create new PRD files\n- Bash(uv run prd validate*) - self-check\n- Bash(git add prds/:*) - staging in prds dir only\n- Bash(git status:*) - status check\n- Bash(git diff prds/:*) - diff in prds dir only\n- Bash(git log:*) - read-only history\n- NO Edit, NO unscoped Bash\n\n**Task List:**\n1. ensure_worktree\n2. set_status(in-progress) + commit\n3. AgentTask with 3 prompts (role, decomposition-guide, task)\n4. ShellTask(\"validate-children\", cmd=\"uv run prd validate\", on_failure=\"retry_agent\")\n5. set_status(review) + commit\n6. push_branch + create_pr\n\n**Files to Create:**\n- `workflows/planning/workflow.py`\n- `workflows/planning/prompts/role.md`\n- `workflows/planning/prompts/decomposition-guide.md`\n- `workflows/planning/prompts/task.md`\n- `workflows/planning/prompts/verify.md`\n- Tests in `tests/test_planning_workflow.py`\n\n### 10. KEY EXISTING PATHS\n\n- Workflow loader: `/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-228-planning-workflow-initial/src/darkfactory/loader.py`\n- Assignment logic: `/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-228-planning-workflow-initial/src/darkfactory/assign.py`\n- CLI commands: `/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-228-planning-workflow-initial/src/darkfactory/cli.py` (lines 572, 610, 798, 880)\n- Containment helpers: `/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-228-planning-workflow-initial/src/darkfactory/containment.py`\n- Workflow dataclasses: `/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-228-planning-workflow-initial/src/darkfactory/workflow.py`\n- PRD parsing: `/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-228-planning-workflow-initial/src/darkfactory/prd.py`\n- Built-in tasks: `/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-228-planning-workflow-initial/src/darkfactory/builtins.py`\n\n### 11. OTHER RELEVANT PRDs\n\n- **PRD-229** - Hardened planning workflow (with templates, hard path enforcement