n\n### 5. Plan the dependency graph\n\nBefore writing any files, plan the ordering:\n\n- Which tasks must come before others?\n- Which can run in parallel?\n- What's the critical path?\n\n### 6. Write the child PRD files\n\nFor each task, use `Write` to create a new file in `prds/`:\n\n- Filename: `PRD-{parent_number}.{index}-{slug}.md`\n- Include all required frontmatter fields\n- Write substantive body sections (Summary, Requirements, Technical\n  Approach with file paths, Acceptance Criteria)\n\n### 7. Update the parent PRD\n\nRead `{{PRD_PATH}}` again, then write it back with the `blocks:`\nfield updated to include wikilinks to all new children. Preserve\neverything else exactly as-is.\n\n### 8. Validate\n\nRun `uv run prd validate` and fix any errors. Repeat until\nvalidation passes cleanly.\n\n### 9. Stage your changes\n\n```bash\ngit add prds/\ngit status\n```\n\n### 10. Report\n\nPrint a summary of the decomposition:\n\n- How many child PRDs were created\n- The dependency graph (which tasks depend on which)\n- Any decisions or trade-offs you made\n\n### 11. Emit the sentinel\n\nYour final line must be exactly:\n\n`PRD_EXECUTE_OK: {{PRD_ID}}`\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01YNxHh6ncb9A2aowuPWjFN2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01ACB4HZCFp7Pwf99JcmjRuZ","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-228-planning-workflow-initial/workflows/planning/prompts/verify.md","content":"# Verification Retry\n\nThe `prd validate` check failed after your decomposition. The harness\nis giving you one retry to fix the issue.\n\n## Failed check output\n\n```\n{{CHECK_OUTPUT}}\n```\n\n## Your task\n\n1. Read the failure output above carefully. Identify which PRD files\n   have validation errors and what specifically is wrong.\n2. Fix each broken PRD file — common issues include:\n   - Missing required frontmatter fields\n   - Malformed wikilinks (must be `\"[[PRD-ID-slug]]\"` format)\n   - Duplicate PRD IDs\n   - Invalid `parent` references\n   - Invalid field values (bad kind, status, effort, etc.)\n3. If the parent PRD's `blocks:` field is malformed, fix that too.\n4. Re-run `uv run prd validate` to verify the fix.\n5. Stage your changes:\n   ```bash\n   git add prds/\n   git status\n   ```\n6. Emit the sentinel line:\n   - `PRD_EXECUTE_OK: {{PRD_ID}}` on success\n   - `PRD_EXECUTE_FAILED: <reason>` if you cannot fix the issue\n\nYou have **one** retry — if validation fails again after this, the\nharness will mark the PRD blocked.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":214,"cache_read_input_tokens":49569,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":214},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"139194c3-2b15-46fb-ae47-01a4e87ddf0a","uuid":"7e346653-e4cc-4b18-a980-548bf0e112ef"}
